==English==
===Etymology===
From Middle English [[moder]], mother, from Old English [[modor|mōdor]]. Cognates include Greek [[μετερ]], Latin [[mater]], German [[Mutter]], Russian [[мать]] (mat')

===Noun===
'''mother''' (''plural'' '''mothers''')

#<!--DefA-->The woman who gave birth to at least one child. ("''My sister-in-law is a mother.''") 
#<!--DefB-->A female [[parent]]. ("''My mother is dead.''")
<!--"mother of all ..." and "motherfucker" definitions are given separately below because they have different origins-->

